    Three passes successive removal data of A. salmon in the Nivelle river

    SucRemNivelle.Rd

    A dataset containing the successive removal data electofishing of salmon juveniles over 3 passes on 3 years (2003--2005) and 11 sites. Contains missing data.

    Usage

    SucRemNivelle

    Format

    A named list:

    I

    The number of sites (sites x years)

    C1

    The number of captures of the first pass for each site

    C2

    The number of captures of the second pass for each site

    C3

    The number of captures of the third pass for each site

    S

    The area in squared meter that was fished for each site

    AI

    The abundance index of each site

    I_pred

    The number of sites (for prediction)

    AI_pred

    Abundance indices (for prediction)

    Source

    Brun, M., Abraham, C., Jarry, M., Dumas, J., Lange, F., & Prévost, E. (2011). Estimating an homogeneous series of a population abundance indicator despite changes in data collection procedure: A hierarchical Bayesian modelling approach. Ecological Modelling, 222(5), 1069-1079.
